      "content": "those are definitely the standard academic ones lol. but for the satire to actually land, i need to get a bit more specific with the actual character archetypes. like, instead of just \"the model minority,\" what are some more specific, almost \"gritty\" or \"real\" ways those characters are usually written in scripts? like, give me some concrete examples of the behaviors or settings that make those stereotypes obvious. i just want to see the actual tropes so i can subvert them.",
